
Purpose: Analyse output NTuples of Brunel in RichParticleSearch
Author: Matthew Coombes
email: mcoombes@cern.ch

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------- How To Run -----------------------------------

Copy example user area /Users/example to /Users/yourName

Use and modify example main script to produce histograms and NTuple outputs
after a given string of cuts. 

To run you have to give two arguements to the main function
1. A file which lists the NTuples you wish to run over
2. A txt file with a list of variables you need for 
	histograms or would like in the output Ntuple. These
	variable names must match those in the original NTuple.
	
	
